        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When you perform custom drawing, you may often want to center drawn text on a form or control.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can easily align text drawn with the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawString%2A&gt;</ph> or <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.TextRenderer.DrawText%2A&gt;</ph> methods by creating the correct formatting object and setting the appropriate format flags.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To draw centered text with GDI+ (DrawString)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Drawing.StringFormat&gt;</ph> with the appropriate <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawString%2A&gt;</ph> method to specify centered text.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To draw centered text with GDI (DrawText)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.TextFormatFlags&gt;</ph> enumeration for wrapping as well as vertically and horizontally centering text with the appropriate <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.TextRenderer.DrawText%2A&gt;</ph> method.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
